# Local LLM Configuration — agape-sovereign workspace
#
# PRIMARY FALLBACK MODEL: LM Studio qwen3.5-9b-sushi-coder-rl-mlx (local, no cloud, unlimited tokens)
# When Antigravity IDE's default cloud models are exhausted or unavailable,
# this workspace uses LM Studio with qwen3.5-9b-sushi-coder-rl-mlx exclusively.
#
# Rules:
# - If the default model (Claude Sonnet / Gemini) reports rate limits or token exhaustion,
#   switch to Provider: LM Studio, Model: qwen3.5-9b-sushi-coder-rl-mlx
# - DO NOT fall back to any cloud-based unlimited-token provider (OpenRouter, OpenAI, etc.)
# - DO NOT fall back to Ollama
# - LM Studio endpoint: http://localhost:1234/v1 (always local, no network egress)
# - Keep model in memory: LM Studio "Keep Alive" = -1 (persistent across sessions)
# - Context window: 8192+ tokens (set via LM Studio config)
#
# Fallback order:
#   1. Default Antigravity IDE model (cloud, limited tokens)
#   2. LM Studio qwen3.5-9b-sushi-coder-rl-mlx (LOCAL ONLY — this is the hard stop; no further fallback)
#
# This policy is intentional: no cloud provider should receive unlimited token requests
# without explicit user approval per session.

## Model Hierarchy
- **Primary**: Antigravity IDE default (Claude Sonnet 4.6 / Gemini)
- **Fallback**: `lmstudio:qwen3.5-9b-sushi-coder-rl-mlx` via http://localhost:1234/v1
- **No cloud overflow**: If LM Studio is unavailable, stop and notify user
